    <h1>Project LoFi EJS</h1>

    <p>This project is a template for building tiny websites with dynamic content using EJS and Node.js. It provides a
        simple development workflow and includes features like server-side rendering.</p>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Dynamic content generation using EJS templates</li>
        <li>Server-side rendering for faster page loads and SEO</li>
        <li>Firebase hosting for easy deployment</li>
        <li>Automatic server reloading during development with Nodemon</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Node.js (Download and install from <a href="https://nodejs.org" target="_blank">https://nodejs.org</a>)</li>
        <li>npm (Comes with Node.js)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Installation</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Clone the repository or download the ZIP file.</li>
        <li>Open a terminal and navigate to the project directory.</li>
        <li>Install the project dependencies.</li>
    </ol>

    <pre><code class="content">
cd project-directory
npm install
    </code></pre>

    <h2>Development</h2>
    <p>To start the development server, use the following command:</p>

    <pre><code class="content">
npm run dev
    </code></pre>

    <p>This will build the project and start the server. The website will be available at <a
            href="http://localhost:3000" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000</a>.</p>

    <h2>Project Structure</h2>
    <p>The project structure is organized as follows:</p>
    <pre><code class="content">
- project-directory
  
|- modules /*no need to touch these */
    |- build.js /*generates the static files */ 
    |- server.js /*for local development only */
|- src
     |- components
        |- counter.ejs
        |- contactForm.ejs */you can add as many components as you like */
     |- baseTemplate.ejs /*you can add as many templates as you like */
  |- public
     |- /* where static pages are generated  */
  |- firebase.json /* where the routing is configured automatically by npm run build */

    </code></pre>

    <h2>Creating New Pages</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Create a new EJS template file (and any relevant components) in the src directory, e.g.,
            <code>newPage.ejs</code>.
        </li>
        <li>Add the new entry to siteData.json</li>
        <li>Save the new EJS template and run the build script.</li>
        <li>The new page will be generated in the <code>public</code> directory and can be accessed at <a
                href="http://localhost:3000/newpage" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000/newpage</a>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Deployment</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Install the Firebase CLI globally:</li>
    </ol>

    <pre><code class="content">
npm install -g firebase-tools
    </code></pre>

    <ol start="2">
        <li>Authenticate with Firebase:</li>
    </ol>

    <pre><code class="content">
firebase login
    </code></pre>

    <ol start="3">
        <li>Initialize Firebase for your project (if not already done):</li>
    </ol>

    <pre><code class="content">
firebase init hosting
    </code></pre>

    <ol start="4">
        <li>Build and deploy the website:</li>
    </ol>

    <pre><code class="content">
npm run deploy
    </code></pre>

    <p>Your website will now be live on the Firebase hosting URL.</p>

